cs.ET, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the design of optical neural networks (ONNs) and their robustness to imprecise components. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including electronic design automation (cs.ET), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on the design and performance of ONNs for image classification, cs.CV and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses the impact of component imprecisions on ONN performance, cs.ET, cs.AI, and cs.LG are also relevant sub-categories.
